I like this introduction to decision making techniques at Creative Market.
&ldquo;Some decisions appear to be relatively straight forward until you take a step back and look at the entire picture with a fresh perspective. You may notice that there are a variety of factors that actually impact a choice or decision that you did not notice before.&rdquo;
The post also features a nice mind map example from Learning Fundamentals focused on personal actions for reducing climate change impacts.

Disturbing article by Lester Brown on the PRI website
&ldquo;..Put simply, saving the Amazon rainforest now depends on curbing the growth in demand for soybeans by stabilizing population worldwide as soon as possible. And for the world’s more affluent people, it means eating less meat and thus slowing the growth in demand for soybeans…&rdquo;
Where was once pristine Amazon rainforest, soybean harvesters march across the landscape instead.

Great post from HBR that calls out the danger of simplifying your dreams down to a narrow outcome that can setup a black and white success or failure scenario. One tool they describe to help avoid this is the &ldquo;folder of gratitude&rdquo;
Diversify Your Dreams
So how do you start moving from one dream to many? A practical tip I&rsquo;ve seen work well is to develop a &ldquo;folder of gratitude,&rdquo; a constantly-updated list of all the things in life you&rsquo;re grateful for.
